As will be remembered, Michoacán did not homolog its Political Constitution or its State Electoral Code or Its Electoral Justice Act, since the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal deadline so that they could enter into force in the present electoral process and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted their publication within the time limits provided for in the Law of the Official Newspaper of the State , on the grounds that he had some objections.
