In this way, the partial count of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may occur in cases where: the results of the minutes do not match; there is no counting and counting record in the box file or it is not held by the chair of the box; or, where there are obvious errors or alterations to the minutes.
In addition, the total count of the vote received at all polling stations in the election may be carried out where there is evidence that the difference between the alleged candidate winning the election concerned and the candidate who has obtained second place in the vote is equal to or less than one percentage point; provided that at the start of the session there is the express request of the party representative and/or coalition who nodded to the second of the designated candidates.
The total count of the vote may also be carried out if, at the end of the ordinary count, it is established that the difference between the allegedly winning candidate and the second candidate is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the express request of the representative of the political party whose candidate came second, in which case the electoral packages that have been partially counted will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that in this situation is the election of Morelia, where according to the PREP the difference between first and second place is only 0.16 per cent, although without accounting for the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
