The whole of Europe is the one that folds under the orders of markets and rating agencies, which suffer from its impotence and lack of solidarity.
It is the whole of Europe that suffers from a humiliation in the international sphere.
We care about the transfer of sovereignty to Europe, but it is the whole of Europe that slowly loses sovereignty and, with it, each of its nations.
The most urgent thing is that popular sovereignty regains the helm of the European project.
Because only together can Europeans reduce the weight of their debts, free themselves from markets and prepare their future through investment.
