But to think of it without greater political and democratic integration, and without it being lived as such by citizens, would be a new madness and lead us to a new s leading point.
We must take on a new stage of European construction.
To build the Republic in France, it was necessary to "make" republicans.
The Interest-Motivated Revolution would not be enough.
This lesson remains applicable.
We must build a more economically integrated Europe.
It can only be achieved by building a more politically democratic Europe, a true European popular sovereignty.
To build Europe, let's make Europeans.
